Agus,

robustbase just installed fine on my stock 8.04 system.  Please make 
sure that you have added all the repositories and packages suggested on 
this page:

http://cran.r-project.org/bin/linux/ubuntu/

Backports are important, and make sure you have r-base-dev
installed.  You may also need to be root (via sudo) to install, although 
there are instructions for local installation.  You can run the 
following commands to see what R related packages you have installed.

dpkg --get-selections | grep r-base
dpkg --get-selections | grep r-cran

Michael

